1
00:00:23,125 --> 00:00:24,583
[NARRATOR]
What was once mainstream

2
00:00:24,666 --> 00:00:25,916
has been far surpassed

3
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:28,500
in the holy land
of personal expression.

4
00:00:28,583 --> 00:00:30,291
The capital of
the former nation,

5
00:00:30,375 --> 00:00:32,083
known now as Always Comima.

6
00:00:44,833 --> 00:00:46,083
Ha!

7
00:00:50,833 --> 00:00:52,541
[NARRATOR]
After the disbandment

8
00:00:52,625 --> 00:00:54,166
of the legendary vigilante squad

9
00:00:54,250 --> 00:00:56,833
of the Third District,
Tokyo Always,

10
00:00:56,916 --> 00:00:59,666
a cosplaying state vigilante
squad was created

11
00:00:59,750 --> 00:01:01,333
to restore the public order.

12
00:01:03,125 --> 00:01:06,333
They're known as...
Knights of the Twin Towers.

13
00:01:06,416 --> 00:01:07,875
[MAN 1]
Hey! Stop, thief!

14
00:01:07,958 --> 00:01:09,166
[MAN 2]
Get back here!

15
00:01:09,250 --> 00:01:11,208
[WOMAN]
Won't somebody stop him?

16
00:01:12,625 --> 00:01:14,000
[NARRATOR]
And leading the squad,

17
00:01:14,083 --> 00:01:15,666
a knight in shining armor!

18
00:01:16,833 --> 00:01:19,208
That sword is
a truly unique weapon.

19
00:01:27,541 --> 00:01:30,708
Its targeted attack
doesn't cause collateral damage

20
00:01:30,791 --> 00:01:33,541
or harm nearby Rests.

21
00:01:33,625 --> 00:01:36,666
The captain of the Knights is
a small Best with a big name.

22
00:01:36,750 --> 00:01:40,500
People call her... Thunderoad!

23
00:01:42,833 --> 00:01:45,583
These are
the guardians of Comima.

24
00:01:46,916 --> 00:01:49,375
[RICK AND SHAW]
Fighting Buddies, Rick and Shaw!

25
00:01:51,166 --> 00:01:52,583
[NARRATOR]
On or off duty,

26
00:01:52,666 --> 00:01:54,833
they are always Comima.

27
00:03:27,625 --> 00:03:29,708
[whistling]

28
00:03:46,041 --> 00:03:47,416
[NOZOMI]
That looks like--

29
00:03:47,500 --> 00:03:49,333
Is that a Moonlight Stone?

30
00:03:49,416 --> 00:03:50,625
[CHIAYA]
Core.

31
00:03:50,708 --> 00:03:52,291
[NOZOMI]
Uh... Core?

32
00:03:52,375 --> 00:03:54,791
[AI]
Oh, wow! It's really pretty!

33
00:03:54,875 --> 00:03:57,791
Y'know, I feel like
I've seen this somewhere before.

34
00:03:57,875 --> 00:03:59,750
[grunts]

35
00:04:01,333 --> 00:04:02,875
Possible.

36
00:04:02,958 --> 00:04:04,166
There are more.

37
00:04:04,250 --> 00:04:05,541
[YUKINA]
And you want what?

38
00:04:05,625 --> 00:04:06,791
To gather them all up?

39
00:04:06,875 --> 00:04:07,916
[CHIAYA]
Yeah.

40
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:10,083
[NOZOMI]
Hold on. this looks just like--

41
00:04:10,166 --> 00:04:12,750
[MASAMI]
Nozomi! [crying]

42
00:04:17,250 --> 00:04:18,250
[NOZOMI]
How can these things

43
00:04:18,333 --> 00:04:19,750
even be gathered?

44
00:04:19,833 --> 00:04:20,708
[YUKINA]
Yeah.

45
00:04:20,791 --> 00:04:21,625
[AI]
That's totally cool.

46
00:04:21,708 --> 00:04:22,583
Where'd you buy it?

47
00:04:22,666 --> 00:04:24,041
[CHIAYA]
I didn't buy it.

48
00:04:24,125 --> 00:04:25,541
I found it.

49
00:04:25,625 --> 00:04:27,375
Okay, then
where did you find it?

50
00:04:27,458 --> 00:04:28,666
In the window.

51
00:04:28,750 --> 00:04:29,666
What?

52
00:04:34,250 --> 00:04:35,291
[ALL gasp]

53
00:04:37,166 --> 00:04:38,375
[AI]
What the--?

54
00:04:43,416 --> 00:04:44,791
Pretty morning.

55
00:04:44,875 --> 00:04:45,958
Huh?

56
00:04:48,166 --> 00:04:49,375
[YUKINA]
Do the birds always come

57
00:04:49,458 --> 00:04:50,708
hang out with you like that?

58
00:04:50,791 --> 00:04:51,875
[NOZOMI]
That's what I thought.

59
00:04:51,958 --> 00:04:53,250
[AI]
What?

60
00:04:53,333 --> 00:04:55,041
That the stone just sort of
appeared in the sky

61
00:04:55,125 --> 00:04:57,041
floating in the middle
of the air, like this.

62
00:04:57,125 --> 00:04:58,833
Or a sparrow
picked one up somewhere.

63
00:04:58,916 --> 00:05:00,333
What, and mine too?

64
00:05:00,416 --> 00:05:02,916
I think I read about
things like this somewhere.

65
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:06,041
About power stones that rain
down mysteriously from the sky.

66
00:05:06,125 --> 00:05:07,708
--[NOZOMI] Really?
--[AI] Power stones?

67
00:05:07,791 --> 00:05:12,041
In fact, I think the Tokorozawa
captain had one, didn't she?

68
00:05:12,125 --> 00:05:13,958
Yeah.
That's what I was talking about.

69
00:05:14,041 --> 00:05:15,250
I gave it to her.

70
00:05:15,333 --> 00:05:17,416
Well, the Higashi Murayama
leader had one, too.

71
00:05:17,500 --> 00:05:18,291
Huh?

72
00:05:19,916 --> 00:05:21,125
Oh yeah, that's right!

73
00:05:21,208 --> 00:05:23,583
The stone on Shigyo's neck
did look like this.

74
00:05:23,666 --> 00:05:25,375
[grunts]

75
00:05:25,458 --> 00:05:26,666
[YUKINA]
Maybe what I read

76
00:05:26,750 --> 00:05:28,416
actually had
a little truth to it.

77
00:05:28,500 --> 00:05:30,375
I've seen something similar
in Tokyo.

78
00:05:30,458 --> 00:05:32,166
I don't know if they're
the same thing, though.

79
00:05:32,250 --> 00:05:34,166
[ALL gasp]

80
00:05:34,250 --> 00:05:36,208
'Kay, so that's
what we're doing, then?

81
00:05:36,291 --> 00:05:38,666
Works for me.
I don't mind going to Tokyo.

82
00:05:38,750 --> 00:05:39,750
[NOZOMI]
We'll just follow you.

83
00:05:39,833 --> 00:05:40,875
Sound good?

84
00:05:40,958 --> 00:05:42,083
Uh... Uh-huh.

85
00:05:44,708 --> 00:05:45,916
[NOZOMI]
Uh, Yukina?

86
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:47,166
What's up?

87
00:05:47,250 --> 00:05:49,500
Hey, uh, Tokyo's that way.

88
00:05:56,541 --> 00:05:58,583
[snoring]

89
00:05:58,666 --> 00:05:59,958
[gasps]

90
00:06:00,041 --> 00:06:01,208
Mmm.

91
00:06:02,583 --> 00:06:03,916
--[CHIAYA] Mmm?
--[NOZOMI gasps]

92
00:06:06,958 --> 00:06:08,750
Uh...

93
00:06:08,833 --> 00:06:10,125
[NOZOMI screams]

94
00:06:15,083 --> 00:06:16,333
[crow caws]

95
00:06:16,416 --> 00:06:18,583
Don't be so sulky, Garm.

96
00:06:18,666 --> 00:06:21,041
We have more
squad members now.

97
00:06:21,125 --> 00:06:23,583
They've gotten really good
at keeping things organized.

98
00:06:23,666 --> 00:06:26,083
Crime prevention
is on the rise.

99
00:06:26,166 --> 00:06:28,166
The fact that I have
less work now,

100
00:06:28,250 --> 00:06:30,333
it's actually a good thing
for Comima.

101
00:06:31,625 --> 00:06:34,000
I have one more job
as captain to complete.

102
00:06:34,083 --> 00:06:36,541
One more criminal element
to subdue.

103
00:06:40,333 --> 00:06:42,250
[caw]

104
00:06:42,333 --> 00:06:45,083
Once that's done,
I'll come back here and buy you.

105
00:06:45,166 --> 00:06:47,708
My dear Prince Rick!

106
00:06:47,791 --> 00:06:48,708
[gasps]

107
00:06:48,791 --> 00:06:50,666
Garm, you crazy bird!

108
00:06:50,750 --> 00:06:53,041
What are you doing to him?
Come down here!

109
00:06:53,125 --> 00:06:55,708
Get your pecky beak
off my prince, you hear me?

110
00:06:55,791 --> 00:06:57,708
[GIRL]
Captain! I've got bad news!

111
00:06:57,791 --> 00:06:59,750
Hey, Noriko. What is it?

112
00:07:00,958 --> 00:07:02,583
[NORIKO]
It's the Dynamite Bombers!

113
00:07:02,666 --> 00:07:04,458
We've had another
warning note from them.

114
00:07:04,541 --> 00:07:05,458
I brought it for you.

115
00:07:05,541 --> 00:07:07,000
Another one?

116
00:07:07,083 --> 00:07:08,291
[NOZOMI]
I'm starting to get

117
00:07:08,375 --> 00:07:09,708
a little nervous now.

118
00:07:09,791 --> 00:07:11,791
Tokyo's a scary place, right?

119
00:07:11,875 --> 00:07:13,458
According to my brother,

120
00:07:13,541 --> 00:07:14,791
the countries are all
pretty similar

121
00:07:14,875 --> 00:07:16,958
when you get right down to it,
so I'm not sure.

122
00:07:17,041 --> 00:07:18,583
Oh, I didn't know
you had a brother.

123
00:07:18,666 --> 00:07:20,583
He's older.
Anyway, Tokyo.

124
00:07:20,666 --> 00:07:22,333
I can say that
the people who helped me

125
00:07:22,416 --> 00:07:24,708
when I collapsed on the street
were very friendly.

126
00:07:24,791 --> 00:07:26,125
[NOZOMI]
Does this "collapsing" thing

127
00:07:26,208 --> 00:07:28,000
--happen often?
--[YUKINA] Yes.

128
00:07:28,083 --> 00:07:30,666
Sometimes I find
I have no idea where I am.

129
00:07:30,750 --> 00:07:32,083
I know where I'm going,

130
00:07:32,166 --> 00:07:34,291
but I just can't seem to
get there for some reason.

131
00:07:34,375 --> 00:07:35,875
[NOZOMI]
Oh, really?

132
00:07:35,958 --> 00:07:37,375
Strange, right?

133
00:07:37,458 --> 00:07:39,958
I mean it's not like I'm
bad with directions or anything.

134
00:07:40,041 --> 00:07:42,291
[NOZOMI]
No. No. Of course not.

135
00:07:45,208 --> 00:07:46,458
Ah!

136
00:07:46,541 --> 00:07:49,458
My neck hurts.
I musta slept on it funny.

137
00:07:49,541 --> 00:07:51,125
Wait. What the--?
Where am I?

138
00:07:51,208 --> 00:07:53,375
What's going on?
Who're you?

139
00:07:53,458 --> 00:07:54,875
Oh, right.

140
00:07:54,958 --> 00:07:55,958
[NOZOMI]
And this chick's

141
00:07:56,041 --> 00:07:56,875
all over the place.

142
00:07:56,958 --> 00:07:57,916
[groans]

143
00:07:58,000 --> 00:07:59,208
[CHIAYA gasps]

144
00:07:59,291 --> 00:08:00,333
[NOZOMI]
And what's the deal

145
00:08:00,416 --> 00:08:02,250
with the mask?

146
00:08:02,333 --> 00:08:04,500
[AI whistling]

147
00:08:04,583 --> 00:08:05,833
[NOZOMI]
I guess everybody's

148
00:08:05,916 --> 00:08:07,666
a little strange
in their own way.

149
00:08:07,750 --> 00:08:09,041
[gasps]

150
00:08:09,125 --> 00:08:10,500
Hey, Ai,
is that song you're whistling--

151
00:08:10,583 --> 00:08:11,583
[YUKINA]
Are you going to go?

152
00:08:11,666 --> 00:08:12,791
The light turned green.

153
00:08:12,875 --> 00:08:14,208
[gasps]

154
00:08:15,958 --> 00:08:17,083
[NOZOMI]
I'm sorry.

155
00:08:17,166 --> 00:08:18,208
[AI]
You're a terrible driver,

156
00:08:18,291 --> 00:08:19,500
y'know that?

157
00:08:19,583 --> 00:08:21,208
Yeah? Then maybe you'd
like to drive instead.

158
00:08:21,291 --> 00:08:22,166
[AI]
I already told you.

159
00:08:22,250 --> 00:08:23,333
I can't drive.

160
00:08:23,416 --> 00:08:24,666
[groans]

161
00:08:24,750 --> 00:08:26,583
Well, then shut your mouth
and quit complaining.

162
00:08:28,041 --> 00:08:29,250
[MAN 1]
Did you find it?

163
00:08:29,333 --> 00:08:30,416
[MAN 2]
No.

164
00:08:31,666 --> 00:08:33,583
[MOMIYAMA]
Stolen? That's unfortunate.

165
00:08:34,625 --> 00:08:36,041
[AKI]
By the time I received

166
00:08:36,125 --> 00:08:38,791
the warning note,
it was already gone.

167
00:08:38,875 --> 00:08:40,208
Looks to me like
this was written on

168
00:08:40,291 --> 00:08:42,000
old-fashioned gridded
writing paper.

169
00:08:42,083 --> 00:08:44,000
I take it it's from
the Dynamite Bombers again?

170
00:08:44,083 --> 00:08:45,375
[AKI]
I won't let them

171
00:08:45,458 --> 00:08:46,916
get away next time!

172
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:49,000
Yes, well,
regardless of your intentions,

173
00:08:49,083 --> 00:08:50,583
until these people are caught,

174
00:08:50,666 --> 00:08:52,791
you won't be able to give us
the stone as per our agreement.

175
00:08:52,875 --> 00:08:55,000
If you manage to
retrieve it from them, however,

176
00:08:55,083 --> 00:08:57,208
I'm prepared to keep
my end of the bargain.

177
00:09:01,291 --> 00:09:02,750
Those dirty bastards.

178
00:09:02,833 --> 00:09:05,375
It's time I put a stop
to their mischief!

179
00:09:06,708 --> 00:09:08,416
[FEMALE GUARD]
Lemme see yer passports.

180
00:09:08,500 --> 00:09:10,375
Hmm. Huh.

181
00:09:10,458 --> 00:09:11,916
You seem nervous.

182
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:13,916
Y'all wouldn't happen to be
Dynamite Bombers, would ya?

183
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:15,125
[NOZOMI]
Huh?

184
00:09:15,208 --> 00:09:16,875
You know, those guys
that caused all the fuss

185
00:09:16,958 --> 00:09:18,166
about six months ago.

186
00:09:18,250 --> 00:09:19,958
The Knight Squad captain
had somethin' important

187
00:09:20,041 --> 00:09:22,416
stolen from her this mornin',
so we gotta be extra careful

188
00:09:22,500 --> 00:09:24,500
about what kinda folks
we let in here.

189
00:09:24,583 --> 00:09:26,750
Interesting accent
for someone in the city.

190
00:09:26,833 --> 00:09:29,166
Probably because
she's a checkpoint worker.

191
00:09:29,250 --> 00:09:30,791
Most of them are
assigned from countries

192
00:09:30,875 --> 00:09:33,041
that have no vested interest
in local affairs.

193
00:09:33,125 --> 00:09:35,208
Huh. What's the Knight Squad?

194
00:09:35,291 --> 00:09:36,625
[GUARD]
Here.

195
00:09:36,708 --> 00:09:39,500
[sighs] This'll give ya
all the information ya need.

196
00:09:39,583 --> 00:09:42,291
Their full name is
the Knights of the Twin Towers.

197
00:09:42,375 --> 00:09:43,875
They're the state
vigilante squad

198
00:09:43,958 --> 00:09:45,958
who do the peacekeeping
in Always Comima.

199
00:09:46,041 --> 00:09:49,208
Wow!
Is their captain really strong?

200
00:09:49,291 --> 00:09:50,708
[GUARD]
Well, yeah. Of course she is.

201
00:09:50,791 --> 00:09:52,833
A Best with a backbone of iron,

202
00:09:52,916 --> 00:09:55,875
which ya wouldn't expect,
given how tiny and cute she is.

203
00:10:01,250 --> 00:10:03,125
[AI]
Ugh.

204
00:10:03,208 --> 00:10:05,666
It's kinda hot
and gross here, huh?

205
00:10:05,750 --> 00:10:08,625
[grunts]
Strange cloud.

206
00:10:08,708 --> 00:10:10,000
[YUKINA]
Oh, that?

207
00:10:10,083 --> 00:10:12,083
Around here it's called
the Comima Cloud.

208
00:10:12,166 --> 00:10:14,791
The festival is a non-stop,
year-round thing.

209
00:10:14,875 --> 00:10:17,791
I heard the Cloud is created
by all the body heat.

210
00:10:17,875 --> 00:10:19,458
It keeps growing.

211
00:10:19,541 --> 00:10:21,250
In the past,
the festival was only held

212
00:10:21,333 --> 00:10:22,541
in that big building there.

213
00:10:22,625 --> 00:10:24,708
I can see why
people would want to leave.

214
00:10:24,791 --> 00:10:26,041
I mean, come on.

215
00:10:26,125 --> 00:10:27,750
You have to admit, though,
it is a little cute.

216
00:10:34,666 --> 00:10:36,583
Hey, Nozomi, look! Over there!

217
00:10:36,666 --> 00:10:37,916
Huh?

218
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:39,666
[GIRL 1] Did you see that
they're making a movie?

219
00:10:39,750 --> 00:10:42,125
[gasps] Come on, Chi, let's go!

220
00:10:43,458 --> 00:10:44,375
[gasps]

221
00:10:44,458 --> 00:10:46,291
[NOZOMI]
Hi! Excuse me!

222
00:10:46,375 --> 00:10:47,541
[BOTH GIRLS]
Huh?

223
00:10:47,625 --> 00:10:48,708
I wanted to ask you about that

224
00:10:48,791 --> 00:10:50,041
heart-shaped stone
you're wearing.

225
00:10:50,125 --> 00:10:51,416
[GIRL 2]
Stone?

226
00:10:51,500 --> 00:10:53,208
Oh wait, are you talking about
her security charm?

227
00:10:53,291 --> 00:10:54,458
Cute, right?

228
00:10:54,541 --> 00:10:56,208
They have them on sale
for general use, too.

229
00:10:56,291 --> 00:10:58,416
[NOZOMI]
Security charm, huh?

230
00:10:58,500 --> 00:11:00,041
I guess I jumped the gun
on that one.

231
00:11:00,125 --> 00:11:01,666
I'm sorry about that.

232
00:11:01,750 --> 00:11:02,958
It's okay.

233
00:11:03,041 --> 00:11:05,166
Chi, go ahead
and show them your stone.

234
00:11:05,250 --> 00:11:06,583
[NOZOMI]
We're looking for these.

235
00:11:06,666 --> 00:11:08,291
That's why I asked
about your charm.

236
00:11:08,375 --> 00:11:09,583
Have you seen them before?

237
00:11:09,666 --> 00:11:10,875
[BOTH gasp]

238
00:11:13,708 --> 00:11:14,666
[alarm blaring]

239
00:11:14,750 --> 00:11:15,833
[GIRLS gasp]

240
00:11:15,916 --> 00:11:16,958
What'd we do?

241
00:11:17,041 --> 00:11:17,958
[MAN]
They're here!

242
00:11:18,041 --> 00:11:19,250
It's the Dynamite Bombers!

243
00:11:19,333 --> 00:11:20,375
[gasps]

244
00:11:22,666 --> 00:11:24,375
[GIRLS gasping]

245
00:11:24,458 --> 00:11:26,166
[NOZOMI]
Whoa!

246
00:11:32,666 --> 00:11:33,708
[AKI]
So you four ladies

247
00:11:33,791 --> 00:11:35,041
are the Dynamite Bombers,
are you?

248
00:11:35,125 --> 00:11:36,291
We're not, actually.

249
00:11:36,375 --> 00:11:37,500
[AKI]
Why do you threaten the peace

250
00:11:37,583 --> 00:11:38,875
of Always Comima?

251
00:11:38,958 --> 00:11:41,041
Think you're tough enough
to take on Tokyo?

252
00:11:41,125 --> 00:11:44,208
Where are your headquarters?
How big is your organization?

253
00:11:44,291 --> 00:11:45,583
[AI]
We have no idea!

254
00:11:45,666 --> 00:11:47,041
[AKI]
Since the bombing,

255
00:11:47,125 --> 00:11:48,958
you've only given warnings
about your intended crimes.

256
00:11:49,041 --> 00:11:50,708
Why haven't you acted on them?

257
00:11:50,791 --> 00:11:52,458
[YUKINA]
We don't know!

258
00:11:52,541 --> 00:11:53,500
[AKI]
Hmm.

259
00:11:53,583 --> 00:11:55,250
I see they've trained you well.

260
00:11:55,333 --> 00:11:56,541
No one trained us!

261
00:11:56,625 --> 00:11:57,666
Is that so?

262
00:11:57,750 --> 00:11:59,083
Then would you care to explain

263
00:11:59,166 --> 00:12:01,500
how you came to be in possession
of this Drom Berserker?

264
00:12:01,583 --> 00:12:03,291
What are you doing with my Core?

265
00:12:03,375 --> 00:12:05,541
Maybe your intention was
to thumb your noses at me

266
00:12:05,625 --> 00:12:08,208
or the Knights with your theft,
but this isn't just an orname--

267
00:12:08,291 --> 00:12:09,625
We didn't steal anything!

268
00:12:09,708 --> 00:12:11,708
That stone really does
belong to Chi!

269
00:12:11,791 --> 00:12:13,208
[NOZOMI]
We weren't even in Tokyo

270
00:12:13,291 --> 00:12:14,916
until shortly before
you picked us up.

271
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:16,166
Right, guys?

272
00:12:16,250 --> 00:12:17,375
[YUKINA]
Oh, yeah.

273
00:12:17,458 --> 00:12:18,583
[AKI]
We're making inquiries

274
00:12:18,666 --> 00:12:19,916
into your passports,

275
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:21,583
but even if you
aren't the thieves,

276
00:12:21,666 --> 00:12:23,416
the fact that you have this
makes it clear

277
00:12:23,500 --> 00:12:24,750
that you're aligned with them.

278
00:12:24,833 --> 00:12:26,541
We told you we have
nothing to do with this.

279
00:12:26,625 --> 00:12:27,916
That's the truth.

280
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:29,916
Now stop being a bully
and give her back her stone!

281
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:32,875
Oh, and one more thing.
I heard you were really strong.

282
00:12:32,958 --> 00:12:34,458
Will you make me your disciple?

283
00:12:34,541 --> 00:12:35,708
--[NOZOMI] What?
--[YUKINA] What?

284
00:12:35,791 --> 00:12:38,250
See, the thing is,
I wanna be a drifter Best.

285
00:12:38,333 --> 00:12:40,166
What d'ya say
if I can lay a finger on you,

286
00:12:40,250 --> 00:12:41,500
you agree to train me?

287
00:12:41,583 --> 00:12:43,125
Huh. You intrigue me.

288
00:12:43,208 --> 00:12:44,375
If you can touch me,

289
00:12:44,458 --> 00:12:46,250
I will not simply
make you my disciple.

290
00:12:46,333 --> 00:12:48,583
I'll call you master
and yield the stone.

291
00:12:48,666 --> 00:12:49,916
All right! Let's go!

292
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:51,000
Wait, Ai!

293
00:12:51,083 --> 00:12:52,666
Ah!

294
00:12:55,583 --> 00:12:57,916
[ALL groaning]

295
00:12:58,000 --> 00:12:59,750
[NOZOMI]
So, what do I do now?

296
00:12:59,833 --> 00:13:02,791
Think like Masa.
What would she do?

297
00:13:02,875 --> 00:13:04,375
[MASAMI]
Give that stone back,

298
00:13:04,458 --> 00:13:06,000
you little brat!

299
00:13:06,083 --> 00:13:08,333
That's a no go.

300
00:13:08,416 --> 00:13:10,625
Mmm. Mmm.

301
00:13:10,708 --> 00:13:13,250
[NOZOMI]
Um, do you think it's possible

302
00:13:13,333 --> 00:13:15,000
that your stone
wasn't really stolen?

303
00:13:15,083 --> 00:13:17,166
Maybe it got lost
and you didn't realize it.

304
00:13:17,250 --> 00:13:18,166
[AKI]
What's that?

305
00:13:18,250 --> 00:13:19,916
[cawing]

306
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:22,041
[NOZOMI]
I'll look for it for you!

307
00:13:22,125 --> 00:13:23,291
[cawing continues]

308
00:13:23,375 --> 00:13:24,916
[AKI]
Be quiet! That's enough, Garm!

309
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:26,500
[AI]
How do you plan

310
00:13:26,583 --> 00:13:27,875
to look for it, exactly?

311
00:13:27,958 --> 00:13:30,000
Well, I haven't
figured that out yet.

312
00:13:30,083 --> 00:13:31,875
The city's huge.
It could be anywhere.

313
00:13:31,958 --> 00:13:33,291
Yeah, maybe,

314
00:13:33,375 --> 00:13:35,833
but that stone
rightfully belongs to Chi.

315
00:13:35,916 --> 00:13:37,750
I've got a request to fulfill.

316
00:13:37,833 --> 00:13:39,333
Except instead of
finding more stones,

317
00:13:39,416 --> 00:13:40,958
we lost the one we had.

318
00:13:41,041 --> 00:13:42,333
[AKI]
A request?

319
00:13:42,416 --> 00:13:43,750
[NOZOMI]
Chi is my first client,

320
00:13:43,833 --> 00:13:46,541
and my job was
to gather these stones.

321
00:13:46,625 --> 00:13:49,291
See, Maccha Green
is temporarily unavailable,

322
00:13:49,375 --> 00:13:50,833
so I'm taking on her duties.

323
00:13:50,916 --> 00:13:52,375
Yes, I've heard of her.

324
00:13:52,458 --> 00:13:54,791
Maccha Green,
the notorious peacebroker.

325
00:13:54,875 --> 00:13:56,125
I know she can be reached

326
00:13:56,208 --> 00:13:58,125
through the Tokorozawa
president's office,

327
00:13:58,208 --> 00:14:01,375
but I didn't know she took on
little personal jobs like this.

328
00:14:03,375 --> 00:14:04,458
These two.

329
00:14:04,541 --> 00:14:06,375
I suppose they're
also here to facilitate

330
00:14:06,458 --> 00:14:08,125
during Maccha Green's
temporary absence?

331
00:14:08,208 --> 00:14:09,250
Huh?

332
00:14:09,333 --> 00:14:11,000
Well, I don't know
about that, really.

333
00:14:11,083 --> 00:14:13,291
I'm not. We're just
traveling companions.

334
00:14:13,375 --> 00:14:14,458
That's all.

335
00:14:14,541 --> 00:14:16,250
Yeah, me neither.
I was just hitchhiking.

336
00:14:16,333 --> 00:14:17,750
Pretty much.

337
00:14:17,833 --> 00:14:19,083
Hmm.

338
00:14:19,166 --> 00:14:21,958
[AKI]
Very well. Find it if you can.

339
00:14:22,041 --> 00:14:23,333
[GIRLS]
What?

340
00:14:23,416 --> 00:14:24,958
[AKI]
You have until sundown.

341
00:14:25,041 --> 00:14:27,625
If you are able to
locate my stone by that time,

342
00:14:27,708 --> 00:14:29,458
I will return this to you.

343
00:14:29,541 --> 00:14:30,583
[GIRLS gasp]

344
00:14:30,666 --> 00:14:32,625
[AKI]
However, if you do not find it,

345
00:14:32,708 --> 00:14:34,291
then all four of you...

346
00:14:35,333 --> 00:14:37,291
will receive
capital punishment.

347
00:14:37,375 --> 00:14:38,583
[cawing]

348
00:14:40,250 --> 00:14:41,416
[CHIAYA ]
Capital?

349
00:14:42,791 --> 00:14:44,083
[HINAYO]
If all you're going to do

350
00:14:44,166 --> 00:14:45,375
is worry,

351
00:14:45,458 --> 00:14:47,250
why did you let Nozomi go
in the first place?

352
00:14:47,333 --> 00:14:49,625
[whimpering]

353
00:14:49,708 --> 00:14:51,291
[TOMOMORI]
Well, because

354
00:14:51,375 --> 00:14:53,958
she's getting to that age where
girls start to hate their dads.

355
00:14:54,041 --> 00:14:55,166
I was trying to

356
00:14:55,250 --> 00:14:57,083
rack up some points with her
while I could.

357
00:14:57,166 --> 00:14:58,750
You know
you're impossible, right?

358
00:14:58,833 --> 00:15:00,083
You let our daughter

359
00:15:00,166 --> 00:15:01,791
go traipse about the world
so she would like you?

360
00:15:01,875 --> 00:15:03,333
I don't see how
you can be so calm

361
00:15:03,416 --> 00:15:04,750
at a time like this, Hina!

362
00:15:04,833 --> 00:15:06,541
Who knows what's happening
to our Nozomi right now?

363
00:15:06,625 --> 00:15:07,916
[HINAYO]
Take a breath.

364
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:10,333
She made a brave decision
to take Masami's place

365
00:15:10,416 --> 00:15:12,333
and travel the countryside
to help people.

366
00:15:12,416 --> 00:15:13,875
We supported her,
and that's that.

367
00:15:13,958 --> 00:15:15,291
[whimpering]

368
00:15:15,375 --> 00:15:17,291
[MASAMI]
Ma'am, is that really true?

369
00:15:17,375 --> 00:15:19,041
[HINAYO and TOMOMORI]
What are you doing here?

370
00:15:19,125 --> 00:15:20,166
[MASAMI]
You don't have to worry.

371
00:15:20,250 --> 00:15:21,500
I'll bring her back to you.

372
00:15:21,583 --> 00:15:23,583
You can't do that!
You're still badly injured!

373
00:15:23,666 --> 00:15:25,041
Ah, nah, I'll be fine.

374
00:15:25,125 --> 00:15:27,208
Really, I feel like I'm
completely healed already!

375
00:15:27,291 --> 00:15:28,458
Here, y'see?

376
00:15:28,541 --> 00:15:29,708
[gasps]

377
00:15:29,791 --> 00:15:31,250
[HINAYO]
What are you doing?

378
00:15:31,333 --> 00:15:32,791
--[TOMOMORI] Masami!
--[HINAYO] Masami, wake up!

379
00:15:32,875 --> 00:15:34,208
[TOMOMORI]
I think she lost consciousness!

380
00:15:34,291 --> 00:15:35,208
Masami!

381
00:15:38,125 --> 00:15:39,833
[MASAMI]
I can't believe this!

382
00:15:39,916 --> 00:15:42,416
If only I still had
my Moonlight Stone,

383
00:15:42,500 --> 00:15:44,958
I'd be better already.

384
00:15:45,041 --> 00:15:48,250
Hey, Shigyo! You had a stone
like mine, didn't you?

385
00:15:48,333 --> 00:15:50,083
I know we're not buds,
but could you lend--

386
00:15:50,166 --> 00:15:51,250
[gasps]

387
00:15:53,083 --> 00:15:54,416
[OTONASHI]
It's no use!

388
00:15:54,500 --> 00:15:57,083
I'm so sorry!
I swear I've looked hard,

389
00:15:57,166 --> 00:15:59,875
but I can't find your
Heroic Garnet at... all.

390
00:15:59,958 --> 00:16:01,458
[MASAMI groaning]

391
00:16:05,458 --> 00:16:06,541
[AKI]
Those girls

392
00:16:06,625 --> 00:16:08,083
are definitely Rests.

393
00:16:08,166 --> 00:16:10,333
They're probably pretending
to search for the stone

394
00:16:10,416 --> 00:16:13,166
to buy time until their friends
can come and save them.

395
00:16:13,250 --> 00:16:15,000
That's why I let them go.

396
00:16:15,083 --> 00:16:17,958
We can tail them and catch
them all in one fell swoop.

397
00:16:20,166 --> 00:16:21,333
[YUKINA]
I really don't think

398
00:16:21,416 --> 00:16:22,875
we'll be able to find it.

399
00:16:22,958 --> 00:16:25,291
I mean, she did say
it was stolen, remember?

400
00:16:25,375 --> 00:16:26,375
[NOZOMI]
We have to

401
00:16:26,458 --> 00:16:28,000
at least look, though.

402
00:16:28,083 --> 00:16:31,541
I am really sorry I got you guys
involved in this mess, too.

403
00:16:31,625 --> 00:16:32,750
[AI]
Why are you being so stubborn

404
00:16:32,833 --> 00:16:34,958
about the whole thing, anyway?

405
00:16:35,041 --> 00:16:38,833
I made a promise...
even if it was just to myself.

406
00:16:38,916 --> 00:16:41,708
She can't do this, so I will.

407
00:16:44,125 --> 00:16:45,125
[gasps]

408
00:16:46,500 --> 00:16:47,708
[AI]
You can't expect to search

409
00:16:47,791 --> 00:16:48,958
the entire city.

410
00:16:49,041 --> 00:16:49,916
[NOZOMI]
I don't know

411
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:51,083
what else to do at this point.

412
00:16:51,166 --> 00:16:52,166
[CHIAYA]
Bushy bush.

413
00:16:52,250 --> 00:16:53,208
[NOZOMI/AI/YUKINA]
Huh?

414
00:16:53,291 --> 00:16:54,458
[YUKINA]
I'm sorry,

415
00:16:54,541 --> 00:16:56,166
what are you talking about?

416
00:16:56,250 --> 00:16:57,750
That's what
the crow was saying.

417
00:16:57,833 --> 00:17:00,458
"Inside bushy bush.
Look bushy bush.

418
00:17:00,541 --> 00:17:02,250
Red bushy bush."

419
00:17:02,333 --> 00:17:03,708
'Kay.

420
00:17:03,791 --> 00:17:05,958
Tell me something, Chi-Chi.
What's with these rocks?

421
00:17:06,041 --> 00:17:07,458
Why do you wanna gather them?

422
00:17:07,541 --> 00:17:09,041
Uh...

423
00:17:09,125 --> 00:17:11,333
I want them
because they're so pretty.

424
00:17:11,416 --> 00:17:13,000
[AI]
What? That's it?

425
00:17:13,083 --> 00:17:14,250
[YUKINA]
Hate to break it to you,

426
00:17:14,333 --> 00:17:15,666
but you might have to
give up on this one.

427
00:17:15,750 --> 00:17:16,708
[NOZOMI]
No way!

428
00:17:16,791 --> 00:17:17,833
As Maccha Green's
representative,

429
00:17:17,916 --> 00:17:19,375
I can't let you do that!

430
00:17:19,458 --> 00:17:22,083
We're not
anyone's representatives.

431
00:17:22,166 --> 00:17:24,458
At any rate,
the sun's about to set.

432
00:17:26,666 --> 00:17:27,500
[AKI]
I don't see

433
00:17:27,583 --> 00:17:29,166
any sign of their allies.

434
00:17:33,416 --> 00:17:35,208
[NOZOMI]
Uh. What was that?

435
00:17:35,291 --> 00:17:36,625
[ALL]
Huh?

436
00:17:42,833 --> 00:17:45,958
[whimpering]

437
00:17:49,125 --> 00:17:50,500
[gasping]

438
00:17:52,500 --> 00:17:54,625
[MOMIYAMA]
The agent's recovery fee.

439
00:17:54,708 --> 00:17:57,125
There's a case where it's of
particular sentimental value

440
00:17:57,208 --> 00:17:59,166
to the owner,
so the price is inflated,

441
00:17:59,250 --> 00:18:01,125
which makes it
extremely over budget.

442
00:18:01,208 --> 00:18:02,375
[HARUKA]
That can't be helped.

443
00:18:02,458 --> 00:18:03,916
There's no time
to worry about it.

444
00:18:05,416 --> 00:18:07,208
We still don't have all we need.

445
00:18:07,291 --> 00:18:08,750
[MOMIYAMA]
Unfortunately, we were depending

446
00:18:08,833 --> 00:18:10,791
on Maccha Green's efforts,
so now...

447
00:18:10,875 --> 00:18:12,041
[sighs]

448
00:18:12,125 --> 00:18:15,333
Yes. Her injuries were
exceedingly ill-timed.

449
00:18:15,416 --> 00:18:16,416
Having clients pay for

450
00:18:16,500 --> 00:18:18,041
peacebroker activities
with the stones

451
00:18:18,125 --> 00:18:19,250
was an excellent gambit.

452
00:18:19,333 --> 00:18:20,625
Now we'll just have to
hide the fact

453
00:18:20,708 --> 00:18:21,708
that she's beyond recovery

454
00:18:21,791 --> 00:18:23,333
and have them
send the stones first.

455
00:18:23,416 --> 00:18:24,833
I suppose you're right.

456
00:18:26,500 --> 00:18:27,958
[HARUKA]
You think me contemptible,

457
00:18:28,041 --> 00:18:28,875
don't you?

458
00:18:28,958 --> 00:18:30,125
No. It's not that.

459
00:18:30,208 --> 00:18:31,375
Believe me,

460
00:18:31,458 --> 00:18:33,666
I know that there are
exigent circumstances.

461
00:18:35,750 --> 00:18:37,125
If I may, ma'am.

462
00:18:37,208 --> 00:18:39,208
You should have a meal
with your daughter sometime.

463
00:18:39,291 --> 00:18:41,250
She seems like such
a lonely little girl.

464
00:18:41,333 --> 00:18:42,541
[HARUKA]
You're right. I should.

465
00:18:43,708 --> 00:18:47,166
She needs to be
told about this, soon.

466
00:18:47,250 --> 00:18:49,166
[ALL groaning]

467
00:18:51,375 --> 00:18:52,458
[caws]

468
00:18:59,833 --> 00:19:01,125
[MOMIYAMA]
Very well, then.

469
00:19:01,208 --> 00:19:02,291
We have a deal.

470
00:19:02,375 --> 00:19:04,500
I'll buy your stone
for 100,000 Comima.

471
00:19:04,583 --> 00:19:06,833
Pleasure doing
business with you.

472
00:19:06,916 --> 00:19:09,041
Once I've officially resigned
as captain of the squad,

473
00:19:09,125 --> 00:19:10,500
I'll contact you.

474
00:19:13,791 --> 00:19:15,958
[alarm blaring]

475
00:19:19,166 --> 00:19:21,625
I still want to
honor our deal, Momiyama,

476
00:19:21,708 --> 00:19:24,000
but will you wait until
I catch the Dynamite Bombers?

477
00:19:27,458 --> 00:19:28,791
Huh?

478
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:32,666
[AKARU]
Hey! Excuse me!

479
00:19:32,750 --> 00:19:34,208
I'd like to buy this statue.

480
00:19:34,291 --> 00:19:35,833
Are you the person
I should talk to?

481
00:19:35,916 --> 00:19:36,708
Huh?

482
00:19:36,791 --> 00:19:37,625
[AKARU]
I was waiting for

483
00:19:37,708 --> 00:19:38,750
the price to go down.

484
00:19:38,833 --> 00:19:40,416
Well you have perfect timing!

485
00:19:40,500 --> 00:19:43,708
Right now I can give you a
special price of 50,000 Comima!

486
00:19:43,791 --> 00:19:45,208
No way! That's great!

487
00:19:45,291 --> 00:19:46,583
Whoa, wait just a sec!

488
00:19:46,666 --> 00:19:49,041
Sell it to me!
I'll pay 80,000 Comima.

489
00:19:49,125 --> 00:19:51,416
[MAN]
Oh. Uh...

490
00:19:51,500 --> 00:19:53,500
No, wait! I'll pay 90,000!

491
00:19:53,583 --> 00:19:55,083
I'll give you 100!

492
00:19:55,166 --> 00:19:56,375
110!

493
00:19:56,458 --> 00:19:59,166
Uh, then I guess I offer 120.

494
00:19:59,250 --> 00:20:00,250
[AKARU]
150!

495
00:20:00,333 --> 00:20:02,750
Ugh. 160. I offer 160.

496
00:20:02,833 --> 00:20:04,750
[AKARU]
180,000!

497
00:20:04,833 --> 00:20:06,291
[groans]

498
00:20:06,375 --> 00:20:08,333
200,000 Comima!

499
00:20:08,416 --> 00:20:11,083
[AKI]
Uh! Wait, please don't tell me

500
00:20:11,166 --> 00:20:13,041
she's working with him!

501
00:20:20,375 --> 00:20:21,416
Huh?

502
00:20:23,041 --> 00:20:24,583
[cawing]

503
00:20:24,666 --> 00:20:25,666
[AKI]
Troublemaker!

504
00:20:25,750 --> 00:20:27,041
How'd you get out of your cage?

505
00:20:27,125 --> 00:20:28,500
Come back here right now.

506
00:20:30,541 --> 00:20:33,458
That's my stone!
But what is it doing in there?

507
00:20:33,541 --> 00:20:35,166
Bird, were you
playing a trick on me?

508
00:20:35,250 --> 00:20:36,750
Caw?

509
00:20:38,041 --> 00:20:39,916
You weren't, were you?

510
00:20:40,000 --> 00:20:42,583
It was my own
stupid mistake all along.

511
00:20:43,875 --> 00:20:45,666
